.SH NAME
ifc-to-db-import - Parse an IFC file and write contents to DuckDB


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBifc-to-db import  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Parse an IFC STEP file and write its contents into a DuckDB database.

.PP
The import command streams through the IFC file, extracts entities, properties,
relationships, quantities, and spatial hierarchy, then writes them into typed
DuckDB tables for SQL analysis.

.PP
By default the output file is named after the input (model.ifc → model.duckdb).
Use --output to specify a different path, or --memory for an in-memory database
that is discarded after the command exits (useful for piping into query).

.PP
Use --skip-* flags to omit specific phases, or --only to run a subset. The
--batch-size flag controls insert batching for large models.

.PP
Progress is reported to stderr. Use -q to suppress it, or --output-format json
for machine-readable output on stdout.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--append\fP[=false]
	Append to existing database instead of overwriting

.PP
\fB--batch-size\fP=10000
	Number of entities per batch insert

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for import

.PP
\fB--log-file\fP=""
	Write log output to file

.PP
\fB--memory\fP[=false]
	Use in-memory DuckDB (no file output)

.PP
\fB--only\fP=[]
	Run only specified phases (properties, quantities, relationships, spatial, geometry)

.PP
\fB-o\fP, \fB--output\fP=""
	Output DuckDB file path (default: \&.duckdb)

.PP
\fB--output-format\fP="text"
	Output format: text or json

.PP
\fB-q\fP, \fB--quiet\fP[=false]
	Suppress progress output

.PP
\fB--skip-geometry\fP[=false]
	Skip geometry serialization

.PP
\fB--skip-properties\fP[=false]
	Skip property set denormalization

.PP
\fB--skip-quantities\fP[=false]
	Skip quantity extraction

.PP
\fB--skip-relationships\fP[=false]
	Skip relationship extraction

.PP
\fB-v\fP, \fB--verbose\fP[=false]
	Detailed logging


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--help-json\fP[=false]
	Print help for all commands as machine-readable JSON


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  # Basic import (creates model.duckdb)
  ifc-to-db import model.ifc

  # Custom output path, skip geometry, quiet mode
  ifc-to-db import model.ifc -o output.duckdb --skip-geometry -q

  # JSON output, only properties and spatial phases
  ifc-to-db import model.ifc --output-format json --only properties,spatial

  # Verbose logging to a file
  ifc-to-db import model.ifc -v --log-file import.log
.EE


